word_mean_info__list.difference: 作“商品”解时系经济学名词，也可指日用品。
正式用词，指商业上销售或商家拥有货物的总称。
指上市待卖的商品或货物。多用复数形式。
指“货物”时，可与goods互换，此系美国英语。在英国，freight志指船装货物。
一般生活或商业用词，指销售或购入的商品。
指在需要时可以动用的财产，包括国家土地、矿藏、水力等自然资源或个人的存款及其他财产。
法律和商业用词，指包括全部动产和不动产的资产。
含义较窄，主要指个人动产。
普通用词，含义广。既可指大笔的钱财或物质财富，也可指抽象的精神财富。
含义较estate宽，指个人或团体合法拥有的财产，包括动产与不动产，或临时的财产。
多指地产或建在地面上的房产。

list.abstract: goods（英 [ɡʊdz]，美 [ɡʊdz]），英语单词，作名词为商品；动产；合意的人。例句：Send goods to the quake area.（将货物送到地震灾区。） goods的近义词有merchandise、wares，反义词有evil、evilness、badbad、ness。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, $1.2 billion illegal goods are bought and sold on Silk Road.
yingyinNormal.zh: 目前已经有价值12亿非法商品通过丝路出售。

yingyinNormal.en: You'll have to explain to your kid why you're working at Dick's Sporting Goods.
yingyinNormal.zh: 以后你就得向你的孩子解释，为什么要在体育用品商店工作。

yingyinNormal.en: Think about the purpose of currency, which is to be exchanged for goods and services.

yingyinNormal.en: With this ring, I thee wed. With my body, I thee worship. All my worldly goods, I thee endow.
yingyinNormal.zh: 以这枚戒指，我娶你为妻，以我的身躯，我将崇敬你，以我的一切，与你分享。

yingyinNormal.en: Its economy is the largest on earth and it makes and exports more goods than anywhere else on the globe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 中国是地球上的最大的经济体，生产和出口的商品比全球其它任何地方都多。

yingyinNormal.en: And more small businesses are selling their goods abroad than ever before nearly 300,000 last year alone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而且还有越来越多的中小企业把产品卖到国外，仅去年一年就达到30万家。

yingyinNormal.en: No. That's where we keep the canned goods. Have you completely forgotten everything you learned at orientation?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是放罐头食物的，你忘了每样东西都要放在指定位置吗？

yingyinNormal.en: He specializes in high-value manufacturing, in goods that are worth far more than the cost of their raw materials.
yingyinNormal.zh: 主要是高端产品制造业，那些产品价值都要偏高，相比起它们的原材料。

yingyinNormal.en: That innovation is what made possible our modern consumer culture by enabling a low-unit cost for manufactured goods.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这项创新通过低成本的生产商品造就了现代消费文化。

yingyinNormal.en: If the total amount of currency in circulation increases faster than the total value of goods and services in the economy,
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果流通的货币总数增加得比经济体中的商品和服务价值还要快。

yingyinNormal.en: If the total amount of currency in circulation increases faster than the total value of goods and services in the economy,

yingyinNormal.en: I'm not gonna do anything about it. I love Penny. It's just nice to have a young, attractive woman sniffing around the goods.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我当然是不可能会对她下手啦，我爱佩妮，只是有个年轻貌美的女性对我有意思也很不错嘛。

yingyinNormal.en: When our nation started the interstate highway act, instead of having local commerce, we could get goods coast to coast, top to bottom.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当我们的国家开始实施了州际高速公路法案来代替当地的商业，我们可以获得商品东海岸到西海岸从上到下。

yingyinNormal.en: Fear of foreign competition once led countries to try and produce everything they needed and impose heavy taxes to keep out foreign goods.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对外国竞争感到的恐惧让一些国家决定自给自足，自行生产所有产品，并且向国外的商品收相当重的税。

yingyinNormal.en: We should limit the agenda to a couple of key issues: import tariffs on industrial manufactured goods, and export quotas on rare earth elements.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们得把议程限制在两个关键问题上，工业制品的进口关税, 以及稀土元素的出口限额。

yingyinNormal.en: And here's the thing we're selling more goods Made in America to the rest of the world than ever before. American exports are at an all-time high.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这使得我们将美国制造的产品卖到全球各地，美国的出口也达到历史新高。

yingyinNormal.en: On the other hand, if the money supply remains the same, while more goods and services are produced, each dollar's value would increase in a process known as deflation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 另一方面，如果货币供应量不变，但商品和服务增加，每一分钱的价值就会增加，这过程就叫通货紧缩。

yingyinNormal.en: On the other hand, if the money supply remains the same, while more goods and services are produced, each dollar's value would increase in a process known as deflation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 另一方面，如果货币供应量不变，但商品和服务增加，每一分钱的价值就会增加，这过程就叫通货紧缩。

yingyinNormal.en: And because it's now much easier to move to where the money is, it's increasingly not only goods that cross borders, but people, which has somewhat uprooted Ricardo's theory.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而因为现在资金的流动与汇集更加便利，不只有商品能够流通国界，人们也可以，而这在某种程度上来说也冲击了李嘉图的理论概念。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Digital services include everything from providing a platform for selling <highlight>goods</highlight> and services online to targeting advertising based on user data.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 数字服务包括从提供在线销售商品和服务的平台到基于用户数据的有针对性的广告。

examination_example.sentence: If there is a role for government, it should really be getting involved in providing common <highlight>goods</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果政府能发挥作用的话，它应该真正地参与提供公共财产中去。

examination_example.sentence: Humans are unique in their capacity to not only make tools but then turn around and use them to create superfluous material <highlight>goods</highlight> and superfluous experiences.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人类的独特性在于其不仅能制作工具，且能转而用工具创造出额外的物质商品和额外的体验。
